          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Nanonets OCR S unified inference API provides a robust, low-latency solution for optical character recognition, designed for seamless integration into production systems. This guide focuses on practical steps for API teams to deploy and manage OCR tasks efficiently."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Architecture of Nanonets OCR S Unified Inference API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Nanonets OCR S unified inference API is built on a scalable microservices architecture, supporting RESTful endpoints for image processing. It handles multiple image formats and returns structured JSON responses with extracted text, confidence scores, and bounding boxes. Key aspects include stateless design for horizontal scaling and built-in rate limiting to ensure fair usage."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integration and Authentication Steps"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To integrate the Nanonets OCR S unified inference API, start by obtaining an API key from the dashboard. Use standard HTTP clients to send POST requests to the inference endpoint. Authentication is via API key in the header, and requests must include the image as a base64-encoded string or URL. Ensure error handling for common HTTP status codes like 429 for rate limits or 401 for invalid keys."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance Optimization and Benchmarking"
